More frequent testing of ingredients and finished dishes for E. coli, Salmonella, Campylobacter, Listeria and other pathogens;
Enhanced sanitation and cleaning protocols in restaurants;
Increased scrutiny of suppliers to ensure they are adhering to strict standards; and,
Improved training for restaurant employees on food handling and preparation procedures.
